---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Who is behind Do-chwi, and why this community exists."
>
  <div class="container prose mt-flow">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>About Do-chwi</h1>

    <section class="mt-flow">
      <h2>Who’s behind this</h2>
      <p>
        I’ll keep my name out of it — call me the brewer. I make Korean
        <em>sool</em> for a living, and I’ve been around it long enough that a
        bubbling jar still feels like the most interesting thing in the room.
      </p>
      <p>
        I’ve spent time inside Korea’s brewing industry, working across
        <strong>production</strong>, <strong>quality control</strong>, and
        <strong>new-product development</strong>. A lot of that job was one
        stubborn question: why does the same recipe come out tasting different
        from one batch to the next? Chasing that answer — the temperature that
        drifted, the <em>nuruk</em> that behaved oddly, the day the fermentation
        ran a little too warm — taught me more than any textbook did. Do-chwi is
        where I translate that experience into something you can actually do at
        home.
      </p>
      <p>
        I stay semi-anonymous because I’d rather this be about the brewing than
        about me. Fewer credentials, more jars.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-flow">
      <h2>Why this exists</h2>
      <p>
        Brewing Korean sool outside Korea is harder than it should be. The
        ingredients are unfamiliar, the good information is mostly in Korean, and
        a lot of guides assume you already know what a healthy fermentation
        smells like. Do-chwi is a free guide for anyone abroad who wants to
        brew Korean sool themselves — no shop, no paywall, no masterclass.
      </p>
      <p>
        It’s just me writing down what actually works, in plain English, so you
        can skip a few of the mistakes I already made for you.
      </p>
    </section>

    {/* ── 참여 유도 ─────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="mt-flow">
      <h2>Say hello</h2>
      <p>
        Reading along is enough, but the fun starts when you brew too. Follow the
        <a href="/learn">Learn journal</a> and brew along. Weird batch? Send me a
        photo on Instagram
        <a href="https://instagram.com/do.chwi" target="_blank" rel="me noopener"
          >@do.chwi</a
        > — I’ve probably seen it before.
      </p>
      <p>Gunbae. 🍶</p>
    </section>

    <p class="disclaimer">
      This site is for educational purposes. Always check your local regulations
      before brewing.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
